# Visual backend -- Snapshot (a cell-level golden: content + fg/bg/attrs
# per cell, captured via a real github.com/charmbracelet/x/vt terminal
# emulator fed this tape's CURRENT frame) and Image (the same emulator's
# cells drawn to a PNG via charmbracelet/x/vttest's Drawer, for visual
# inspection -- see snapshot.go and image.go). Source is the same
# sample.ctml the core DSL example (sample_test.ctml) renders, so this tape
# doubles as a second worked example of the same fixture read through a
# different backend.
#
# Expect Fits first: Snapshot/Image size their emulator to this tape's
# resolved Width, so a line that overflowed it would autowrap inside the
# emulator and corrupt every row after -- Expect Fits is what guarantees
# that assumption holds before Snapshot/Image ever run.

Source sample.ctml
Set Width 40

Data session.title "Welcome"
Data version "1.0"
Rows items 3

Expect Fits
Snapshot visual.snapshot
Image visual.png
